properties.description: The former studio home of the sculptor Dora Gordine and her husband the Hon. Richard Hare, a scholar of Russian art and literature. 1930s house over four floors including a flat roof terrace and views of Richmond Park.
properties.name: Dorich House Museum

properties.description: King's Cross is a 67 acre development in Central London being transformed into a new city quarter with 20 regenerated heritage buildings, new homes, offices, public spaces, shops, galleries, bars, restaurants, schools and a university.
properties.name: King's Cross Heritage, Energy Centre and Garden Tours

properties.description: Grade II-listed Georgian domestic building c.1760, formerly part of Bedford Estate. Interior refurbished 1924-5 to form lecture hall (restored 2014), library, bookshop and offices. Oak woodwork and green Doulton tiles line the staircase.
properties.name: The Swedenborg Society

properties.description: Recently refurbished well-executed and colourfully detailed example of Victorian reading and vestry rooms (1863) with added public hall by S Woodridge 1887.
properties.name: Isleworth Public Hall

properties.description: Founded by William the Conqueror's Archbishop Lanfranc in 1080 (the significant crypt survives) St Mary-le-Bow was rebuilt, notably by Wren after the Great Fire and by Laurence King in 1964 after WWII destruction. Home of Bow Bells.
properties.name: The City Churches: St Mary-le-Bow

properties.description: London's main tourist information centre is clad in a specially manufactured system of 220 pre-finished stainless steel panels. The subtly reflective surface provides a striking counterpoint to St Paul's. NOTE: Closed on Monday 19 September
properties.name: City Information Centre

properties.description: The independent cultural centre Pushkin House will contribute to this year's Open House Festival through a programme of events and community initiatives at its Grade-II listed building in Bloomsbury Square.
properties.name: Pushkin House

properties.description: A rare example of a Brutalist Livery Hall which underwent extensive refurbishment in 2016. New Pavilion, exhibition and archive space and garden.
properties.name: Salters' Hall

properties.description: St Anne's Limehouse has been described as 'the finest parish church in England.' Designed by Nicholas Hawksmoor, it is Grade I listed and one of the Major Churches in the Church of England. It is home to a thriving Christian congregation.
properties.name: St Anne's Church, Limehouse

properties.description: Loughborough Pearson's red brick building is unimposing from the outside, but inside is a riot of Gothic Revival design. Golden mosaics reveal the character of the Grade II* listed chapel, built as part of the Middlesex Hospital.
properties.name: Fitzrovia Chapel

properties.description: The Gilbert & George Centre was originally established as a registered charity by the artist in 2009 with the objective to advance the education of the public in the arts, and generally to advance the arts, architecture, heritage, and culture for the benefit of the public.
properties.name: Gilbert & George Centre

properties.description: Cullinan Studio converted this Victorian warehouse into their low-energy office in 2012, retaining 80% of the existing building fabric. The Foundry co-working hub is now home to several organisations working in the built environment.
properties.name: Foundry Co-Working Hub

properties.description: The Nourish Hub turned a vacant post-office into community space where learning about healthy eating and cooking food is used to connect diverse cultures, teach meaningful skills and bring people together.
properties.name: Nourish Hub

properties.description: Repurposed out of a disused sausage factory, Grow was converted into a grassroots venue, community hub, bar and kitchen. This canalside venue is part of an ecosystem of artist studios & small independent businesses & working yard.
properties.name: Grow, Hackney
City & Guilds of London Art School

properties.description:
A great little museum set in the Grade 2 listed Ossulston Estate - a prime example of pre-war Social housing - based on Karl Marz Hof in Vienna.
Open Wednesdays to Saturdays throughout Festival 
Sunday 11th Event
properties.name: People's Museum Somers Town

properties.description: Poroban is a multi-disciplinary design studio, based off Old Kent Road, specialising in low carbon building design. We are offering free design surgeries throughout September and are hosting an open day on Saturday 9th Sept.
properties.name: Poroban studio

properties.description:
A walk to explore Raymond Unwin's aspirations to create a new form of town extension which encompassed the best aspects of town and country. Run by David Davidson of the Hampstead Garden Suburb Trust. 

2 of 3 tours run by the Trust.
properties.name: The Sharing of Great Things

properties.description: Free access to the final weekend of 'we are a group of people composed of who we are', a survey exhibition that traces artistic, cultural and social collective work that took place in Hackney between 1971 and 1986.
properties.name: Peer

properties.description: A residential family home. The architecture and design was created in collaboration with Studio 1 Architecture/Studio Fuse (practice has featured on Grand Designs) and Designer Decoresidence whose founder resides in the property.
properties.name: 33 Buchanan Gardens

properties.description: Architecture for London designed and built a new home for stationers Present & Correct in a heritage retail unit. In a nod to the neighbouring British Museum, cabinets as 'wunderkammer' display the stationery as objects of desire.
properties.name: Present & Correct Stationers

properties.description: Explore the Bush Theatre, West London’s home of new writing. Get a behind the scenes look at our fifty-year history, including how over 2016 we transformed our 128-year-old building into an accessible and sustainable modern theatre.
properties.name: Bush Theatre - Backstage Tours

properties.description: We propose to open the Museum of Croydon stores for an intimate guided tour of our stored collections also featuring an overview of collection care. This activity will take approximately 1hr and can cater for a maximum of 8 people.
properties.name: Museum of Croydon Behind the Scenes Tour

properties.description: Public Tours tours by Architect's DSDHA and the team at National Youth Theatre of the NYT's recently redeveloped RIBA-award-winning building, which created the UK's first theatre dedicated to staging work created by young people.
properties.name: National Youth Theatre

properties.description: Join us for a sustainability-focused open studio at Conran and Partners, award-winning architecture and interior design studio, showcasing the holistic way we integrate sustainable design practices into our work.
properties.name: Design for Life – A Holistic Approach to Sustainability
